facebook.message:
Bingley - Two men jailed after attempted robbery at Bingley supermarket in 2010
Two men from Salford, Greater Manchester aged 32 and 28 years have been jailed for 12 and 11 years respectively at Manchester Crown Court for a robbery conspiracy, which included a raid at Tesco Express store, in Druids View, Crossflatts in November 2010.

Three masked men, armed with a sledgehammer and a crowbar, followed a guard into the shop at 8am, but fled empty-handed when the alarm was raised. Half a dozen customers were in the shop at the time, including at least two Bingley Grammar School pupils. Nobody was injured.

Detective Inspector Stuart Lyons, of Airedale and North Bradford CID, said: “There is no hiding place for these kinds of people. We will always investigate such crimes until we find those responsible, removing the potential threat they pose to our communities.”

The older man pleaded guilty to robbery and conspiracy to commit robbery. The younger man pleaded guilty to conspiracy to rob and conspiracy to steal motor vehicles. The court heard that on Thursday, December 2, 2010, three masked men, armed with a crowbar and sledgehammer went into the HSBC bank on Bradshawgate in Leigh, Greater Manchester.They grabbed a member of staff and a customer, made threats and managed to gain access to the back office from where they stole cash.They only let the member of staff go when they got to the front door of the bank, at which point they ran out and left in a waiting car which sped off.

facebook.message:
Runaway 
By Adam Brownsord

 
Chapter One “The Bullying
“Leave me alone” Rory shouted sitting hugging his legs and crying. The four bullies Trevor, James, Leo and Jack were standing there laughing and Trevor the leader of the gang said “NO! Why would we do that?” Rory Whispered “please, please just go”. Trevor put Rory against the wall and shouted “were you speaking about me?” Rory stayed silent Trevor waited for about 10 seconds and shouted “huh ignoring me yeah? Bad idea you better watch your back.” Rory was petrified but he thought he had to get on with his day so he didn’t tell anyone
. Through the day Rory was getting more scared as the day went on but he hid it with a fake smile. Carly Rory’s friend thought something was wrong but didn’t quite know and she was quite worried about her best friend. Before the next lesson Carly pulled Rory to one side and asked “What’s up bud” Rory replied “nothing look I’m smiling” and put on a fake smile once again to hide the pain. Carly didn’t believe that smile she was the only person that could tell Rory’s proper feelings. Carly then said in a caring voice “Right I know there’s something wrong and I’m going to find out sooner or later. So when are you going to tell me?” Rory started to cry and Carly decided to give Rory a massive hug. Rory explained “I’m getting bullied and it started two days ago.” Carly was shocked that someone would do that to Rory. Carly didn’t know how to reply to that but she found a reply “Come on Rory, lift your head up for me”. Rory head slowly rose as he walked to tutor. 
In Rory’s tutor were Trevor, James, Leo, Jack, Rachay, Jenny, Leah, Carly, Peter, Liam and Julie. In Rory’s head no one in his tutor cares and the boys didn’t but the girls cared about him more than he would ever know. Mrs Lowe, Rory’s tutor she was a very nice teacher probably the nicest at the school. She was the teacher you could trust. She made an announcement that it was her last term at West Lake Secondary School. Everyone was sad except the bullies, they were cheering at the back of the classroom.
 The bell went and everyone left for the next class. Rory was the last one to leave the classroom Carly wanted to see if anything happened as the gang was out just before him so Carly hid. The gang of the 4 boys came behind Rory and followed him for a little while and then attacked him Leo held him still while Trevor, James and jack was punching and kicking Rory. Carly ran over to the pain struck boy rolling on the floor. Carly ran and got some her name was Rachay she was in Rory and Carly’s tutor Rachay ran as fast as she could and got a teacher. The teacher didn’t see what happened so she couldn’t punish anyone and Rachay and Carly was really frustrated. 
In maths Rory was finishing his work but paper kept on being thrown at him with threatening notes. Rory started to cry, everyone was wondering what was happening except from Bullies as they knew Carly and Rachay ran over to see what was wrong. Rory didn’t answer he was too busy drowning in his tears
. It was lunch and Rachay and Carly was sitting with Rory, Rory was still upset from the threats. Rory didn’t eat much and Rachay and Carly was getting worried. Rory was starving himself. Rachay was thinking that but didn’t think it was his sort of thing. Rachay, Carly and Rory was speaking about One Direction’s new album “Take Me Home” and what their favourite song on it. Leo told Trevor what they were talking about it. Trevor approached the table they were sitting at Rory was about to walk away but Trevor grabbed his arm and twisted it Rory began to cry Rachay started to shout At Trevor “What do you think you’re doing? Get of him now!” Trevor laughed and then let go and punched Rory, Rory began to cry. Carly ran and got a teacher she didn’t believe that Trevor did it and when she went Trevor began to laugh as he walked away.
 In tutor and the end of the day Mrs Lowe revealed there will be a new pupil being added to the tutor group. Rory was getting a bit nervous of what their think of him. Loads of different questions went round in his head. Will he be another bully? Or will he be a victim? Will he be a friend? Or Enemy?
It was the end of school everyone went home Rory had to walk home today because his dad was at work and his mum was picking his brother up. Rory was quite scared because he didn’t know if the bullies would be their which they were Rory ran to his house scared as they were following him he called Rachay and she came over to protect him. She felt it was her job to do so Rory didn’t think anyone cared about him but Rachay and Carly definitely did they were there for him always.
 Rory was twelve and his bully s are 12-16 and he hated his life and people hated him so much. On Saturdays he attends a club where people bully him there too so he has about 8 bullies. 
It was Friday and Rory went through his normal routine getting changed, brushing his teeth and eating breakfast etc. Rory was at breakfast when he got a text from a number he hasn’t received a call or text from before. He thought it was the gang of four who bullies him and he was correct. It read “GET READY TO DIE, YOU F****** B***.” Rory was petrified he was right to be too. At school before everyone went to tutor everyone was in the halls and Rory saw the bullies and hoped they didn’t see him. The speakers boomed out “today our new student starts his name is Matthew please help him settle in” it went silent for about 10 seconds but the chatter started again Matthew had to wear name badge to be recognised. Rory was thinking he must be so embarrassed and he was correct. Matthew had been approached by the gang already and he was welcomed and the bullies was being nice for change, probably hoping for a new member. Julie in Rory’s tutor went to speak to Matthew and he wasn’t shy at all. Julie asked “Do you like bullies?” he replied “of course not why” Julie pointed at the four and said “you know them you just spoke to? There the bullies of this school”.   He replied that he want to support the victim of the bullying. Julie led him to Rory. She explained “this is the victim, he might not answer. He’s really shy.” Rory had his head down at the floor and staring at his feet. Matthew said “Hi I’m the new boy I heard you’re being bullied.” Rory Replied “Yeah why” Matthew said “I want to help you”. Rory just laughed. 
On the way to class Matthew did the same as Carly and hid as he wanted to know the bullies were like. The bullies started to insult and threaten him like normal. Matthew came over to the bullies and went face to face and explained “I’ve heard enough of you already and I only just started. STOP BULLYING HIM OR ILL SORT IT OUT!"  Trevor replied “Haha bring it on your new and you sticking up for this t***.” Rory started to cry. Matthew took Rory to one side and said “are they like this all the time?” Rory just nodded. Matthew took him to class.
On Friday after school he started to believe what people was saying didn’t eat at all and started to begin self-harming himself. He would cut his wrists and hands. He didn’t care he just did it yeah it was painful but it was less pain than getting bullied every day and non-stop.   He wanted to end it but he thought of his friends and what they would do and he didn’t want to ruin their lives. He even wondered if they really cared, if they actually were his friends and if Matthew was using him. Rory was getting abuse. Rachay told him to like the page NO Bullying which he did he became friends with the owner Jennifer and Rory made a friend on their called Amanda she was from Ireland and they became pen-pals. She became good friends with Rory and built his confidence like Carly, Rachay, Matthew and Jenny is trying to do. Rory has been holding real emotions all his life as he thought no one cares or wants to listen about his life so he would just smile and when people ask if he’s ok he would say I’m fine. His friends had enough of him lying about his emotions and met up and discussed about it. They wished he would tell the truth so they could sort it out but Rory was worried if telling them would get him more bullied so he decided to suffer in silence. He received a text from Matthew saying he wants to meet up Rory Replied “ok Cool”. Rory walked to the park and Matthew was there with two people Rory hasn’t seen before and he got scared. Matthew said “calm down these are my friends they have been bullied but not as bad as you and I think you will get on well”. Rory just smiled he said nervously “What’s their names?” Matthew replied “Lulu and Lola”.  Rory whispered “Hi” Lulu replied first “Hi what’s up?” Rory replied “Bullies” Lulu said “aw I did but they made me who I am.” Everyone went silent.  Lola thought she should lighten the mood so she said enthusiastically “Hey, I’m Lola. I know how you feel I have been through it before but I’m here to help you”. Rory smiled.

The next day in maths everyone was speaking except from Rory he just sat there hiding his arms. Matthew saw this and told Rachay and Carly to see if it happens all the time. Rachay whispered “Do you think he’s self-harming himself?” Carly said “I hope not do you want me to ask?” Rachay nodded. Carly approached Rory and asked “What’s up? Why are you covering your arms?” Rory replied “Nothing and I’m just cold.” Matthew came over as Carly walked away. Matthew explained “You can tell us mate, were trying to look after you.” Rory whispered to Matthew “I have had enough of my life.” Matthew replied “Let me see your arms.” Rory pulled his sleeves up meanwhile he was crying. Matthew explained “You shouldn’t do this even if you’re getting bullied.” Through the tears Rory explained “I’ve can’t cope anymore even though I couldn’t cope from the beginning.” Matthew nodded to Rachay, Julie, Lulu and Carly to show what they feared has happened. A girl at front called Frankie Rory has never spoken to before because she was quite popular looked and then asked “How did you do that?” Matthew answered for Rory by saying “Why do you wanna know?” Frankie replied “I might be popular but I do care.” Rory replied “I did it myself.” Frankie replied “Why?” Rory whispered “Bullies”. Frankie explained “aww don’t let them get to you.” Rory sadly replied “Too late”. 

At lunch Rory was sitting with Rachay, Julie, Lola, Lulu, Mathew, Carly and Frankie They were speaking about One Direction and Justin Bieber. Then all of sudden Leo starting whispering into Matthew’s ear “You could have been popular” Matthew replied I’d rather be unpopular than a bully.” Leo replied “hahaha your choice”. 
At break Rory wanted some alone time and was walking on the misty field suddenly the gang came over. Rory quietly asked “Can you go away please?” the gang all laughed and James replied “not a chance!” they all teased Rory for about ten minutes. 
 
When they walked away Rory started to cry. Lauren Rory’s big sister came over and softly asked “What’s up bud?” Rory didn’t reply. Rachay came over and told Lauren the whole thing. Lauren gave Rory a massive hug. A tear started to slowly drip down Lauren’s face, she tried to hold them in so Rory didn’t cry more. Rachay asked “can I see your phone please?” Rory nodded Rachay saw all the threats from over 6 different numbers. Rachay asked Lauren “have you seen this?” Lauren looked through all the messages and started to get angry. Rory ran to his room and locked the door and put One Direction on. Carly ran up the stairs and knocked on his room door and in a soft voice asked “can I come in please?” Rory unlocked the door and Carly walked in and saw blood on his jumper. She said “Don’t do this again please for me, for your sister and for Rachay.” Rory cried “I can’t cope with this I couldn’t at the beginning and I can’t now!” Lauren walked in and saw what he has done, she softly explained “Don’t do this ever again! You can go through this I’ll be by your side the whole time”.  

Chapter 2 “Confidence”

Lauren walked to school with Rory, Carly and Rachay.  Rory saw the four boys and hid behind Lauren. Rachay spotted them to and told Lauren that was them. Lauren walked over and asked them “Bullying my little brother are you?” Jack replied “who’s you brother” Lauren replied “Rory” Trevor explained “No were really good friends” Rachay stepped forward and angrily replied “No you’re not I saw you beating him up.” Carly asked “Why? Do you what you’ve made him do? He self-harms, He starves himself and he can’t cope but that’s what you wanted wasn’t it”. Lauren walked away and so did the others.
In the next lesson Lulu was looking after Rory as Lauren was in a different year to them. To be honest the gang didn’t care what Carly and Lauren said and carried on bullying Rory. Rory was feeling mentally weak as usual but he felt a bit more confident in himself and started to answer questions asked to the class. 
 
Later in the day Rory was walking to his locker when Trevor put him up against the wall and explained “Tell one more person and your life is over” Trevor let go and Rory fell to the floor and Trevor started to kick him and punch him. Rory’s nose was bleeding and his arm had loads of bruises on. Lauren ran over and took him to the schools nurse. 
In the nurses room Rory was sitting there crying in pain whilst Lauren was hugging him. The nurse was checking his pulse, Blood pressure etc. The nurse said “Rory will need to come to me once every week for 3 weeks” Lauren replied “ok ill make sure he does”. 

Chapter 3 “Runaway”
Rory couldn’t cope anymore and loads of thoughts were going through his head and he decided he’s going to run away. 
When he got home he posted on Facebook “Time To give in “no one knew what this meant and just left him to live his life. No one knew what Rory was planning. He took his wallet, some food and a drink.
He made sure no one heard the door close and ran as fast as he could to find somewhere no one would no one would know where he is. He ran to a park and hid in the woods and opened his sleeping bag. He prayed for his friends and family.  He took a photo of Lauren with him so he remembered her. 

At home Lauren was going to bed and went to go and kiss goodnight to Rory. She walked in and saw a note on the bed it read:

Dear whoever is reading this?
I love you so much but I’m getting bullied and I can’t cope any more. I have decided to run away and help people and keep them happy because they don’t care about me no one does. So yeah my life is terrible and I have written and rewritten loads of time. I have feel bad about this but I love you guy’s loads. Lauren you an amazing sister and I love you very much. Lulu, Julie, Rachay, Matthew, Lola and Carly I love you guys as family. 
Love Rory
Xxx
Lauren began to cry she was crying so much it didn’t stop for over ten minutes. She rang every friend on the list about Rory running away knowing it was 10:30. Everyone met up and went looking for him. Lauren rang the police. Everyone went looking for him.

The next day at school the speakers blasted “Our best student Rory Green has gone missing, please help look for him.” Lauren went looking for bullies and found them she put Trevor up against the wall and shouted “You did this to him you made him do this and you think its hilarious do you?” Trevor mumbled “Yeah it’s his fault and high fived Leo” Lauren got angry and slapped him.
After school Lauren and the people on the list were looking for Rory. The police couldn’t continue the search and told Lauren. Tears started to pour down her fear filled face Rachay and Carly was comforting her and Rachay said “We WILL find him!” 
Rory didn’t know they were searching for him and started sing and heard Lauren coming singing “Keep holding on” Rory began to cry. He though no one cared about him thou so he stayed silent as he was scared that he was going to get told off he was scared of what was going to happen he thought that the his mum would hate him and Lauren wouldn’t want to speak to him ever again, yeah she was upset but she cared about him more than anyone else would and she wouldn’t give up searching for him. Matthew saw Lauren walking through the bushes and asked “have you found him?” Lauren replied “No you?” Matthew replied “nope” and Carly ran over and shouted “I FOUND HIS COAT!” everyone ran over to where she was. They followed the direction of the coat. They found blood track and was scared something has happened. They found a video camera and it was Rory’s it was speaking and crying he said “whoever is watching this I’m Rory I’m a victim of bullying I have given in but you don’t have to fight bullying for me but all I can say is goodbye”. Tears were sprinting down her face. They decided to carry on searching they saw a sleeping bag in a distance but nobody or no one there Lauren didn’t stop searching. Matthew shouted “I FOUND HIIS BODY!” Lauren ran over and he was knocked out she rang the hospital and they were their five minutes after Lauren called. They took Rory to the hospital.

In the hospital they were worried that too much blood came out of his body, they thought he was dying and would be dead in a couple of hours “BEEP BEEP” an alarm went off Lauren and Carly got worried and it meant he has stopped breathing loads of doctors came in shouting “CLEAR!” and pumped his heart he was breathing again. They filled his body with a blood from a blood transfer patient. The next day Rory woke up to Lauren by his side she said “I told you I’ll always be there for you” Carly was holding Rory’s hand with her eyes close praying he will be ok. Rory kissed her hand and said “I’m alive” Carly was so happy.

Chapter 4 “Home Again”
At school the next day it was tutor when everyone was talking and Rory was talking to Mrs Lowe about what happened and she was so shocked.
Matthew was with Rory nearly all the time today Matthew wouldn’t take his eyes of Rory in case he ran off. Rory had to go to the school nurse to day and get the normal check-up since he was beaten up.

After school Rory ran to the place he felt safe, The hill by his house he would sit up their remembering his best friend that died due to cancer ages ago when he was 5 they would play tag and create swings together and he would never leave Rory which to Rory meant it was his fault it would make him cry but it would give him good memories.  
 
They would all be together since Peters last two minutes which Rory meant it was his fault. Lauren knew where Rory goes every Tuesday and that was the hill so Lauren would let Rory have half an hour alone then come and find him. Lauren would hug him every time he was up their but he would never forget him he cared too much.
At school Rory had treated the same but by what his friends have said had put more self confidence in Rory a lot. The meetings with the school nurse helped his bruise heal and his mind to change a bit so he could hopefully get more confidence in himself. His friends understood him.

At break the gang ganged up on Rory and Matthew. Jack was holding Matthew whilst Leo was punching and kicking him meanwhile James was holding Rory and Trevor was punching him in the face. Rory got his blood in his tears and his tears went red. Matthew was more worried about Rory. He punched Leo and kicked James got hold of Trevor round the neck through him against the wall and pushed James into the wall. Rory asked “why did you do that?” Matthew replied “I have had enough of them hurting you.” Lauren was going to her locker when she saw them on the floor she brought tissues out of her bag and gave them to the two blonde boys.

   Amanda, Rory’s friend of NO Bullying the page on Facebook was video calling Rory when someone came in there and shouted “WHAT DO YOU THINK YOUR DOING” he pushed him to the floor it was his brother who abused him quite a lot. Lauren and he fought all the time. Lauren ran in as she heard crying she saw Rory on the floor. She started shouting “WHAT ARE YOU DOING TO HIM!”  And got him out of the room.

Chapter 5 “Love?”
Ashleigh a popular girl in the class above was texting her friend about how cute Rory looked and about how she has found a new crush. She approached Rory and asked “Hey How are you?” Rory replied ‘don’t hurt me please” she replied “I won’t I think you cute.” Rory did a nervous little laugh. Ashleigh asked for a date and she got it. Rory texted his big sister Lauren “I HAVE A DATE XXX” Lauren replied “YAY XX” She told everyone Rachay, Matthew, Carly, Lulu, Lola and Julie. They were all excited. Matthew, Carly and Rachay all came over to help Rory get ready. Rory wore polo with chinos. 
Ashleigh was with her friends Emily, Abigail and Leonie. The girls were helping Ashleigh get ready for the date she was excited. She doesn’t know Rory was getting bullied. Leonie and Emily already knew Rory and were best friends with him but they only just found out about the bullying and they were going to let Rory tell Ashleigh about the bullies. 
At the restaurant Ashleigh said “you look cute as always Rory” Rory nervous giggle came up again and he replied “You’re beautiful” and Trevor and the gang walked in Rory suddenly put his head down. Ashleigh saw there was something wrong and asked “what’s up?” and Rory answered “you know those four boys” and pointed at Trevor, James, Jack and Leo Ashleigh nodded and Rory explained “their bullying me”. Ashleigh answered “if they come over here I’ll talk to them.”
They ordered what they want to eat meanwhile on the bullies table, Jack spotted Rory and Ashleigh and asked Trevor “is that Rory?” Trevor looked and answered “yeah I’m going to go over there.” Ashleigh saw him coming and asked “what do you want?” Trevor replied “Rory” Rory replied “what?” Ashleigh said “Don’t go with him” Rory said “ok” Trevor said “who is this? Your other sister” Ashleigh replied do you mind insulting my boyfriend?” Trevor replied “You his girlfriend Haha popular date a geek.” Ashleigh just dragged Rory out and they went home kissing.

At home Rory went up to bed and Lauren came in and asked “how was it?” He replied “Amazing although we left earlier than expected due to Trevor” Lauren in a comforting voice explained “Least it went well”
The next day Rory woke up with texts from Ashleigh “let’s get you confidence up and your beautiful Love you xx” Rory replied “I love you too you amazing don’t let anyone tell you different.”

Lauren was with Leonie today as they went shopping for presents for Rory’s birthday. Leonie found a hoodie she thought Rory would love and brought it for him Lauren brought  Rory about 8 presents that day one was a case for his blackberry it had on it Keep Calm And Be A Directioner”. Lauren brought Rory One Direction tickets for 4th of April. Rory would be so happy and Lauren invited 3 friends Rachay, Carly and Leonie. They all kept it a secret and they were really excited.
Meanwhile Rory and Matthew were playing FIFA 13 on the Xbox 360. Rory was really good at it and won every match against Matthew.  Rory was really good at this and he was really good at PES as well he loved every football game there was and he was good at it to.
Ashleigh was getting posts on her Facebook “Haha you’re going out with a geek” and so on. She didn’t care what other people thought to be honest she loved him and he loved her and all that matters. Their relationship was strong it’s like you couldn’t break it.
At school the next day in the playground Rachay, Julie, Ashleigh, Lulu, Carly, Leonie, Matthew and Ashleigh was talking about Rory’s surprise birthday party. It was going to be massive. It is in three weeks. Rory was with Emily, Ashleigh’s friend walking around the playground talking about what happens to him. Trevor came over and said “cheating on her already you dirty scum” Emily replied “No were just friends actually” Trevor didn’t answer he just nodded and pushed Trevor to the floor and laughed and walked away. Rory was in so much pain he fell to the ground. He got helped up by Emily and took him into the class.

Chapter 6 “The Funeral”

At home Rory checked his phone and saw he had threats from loads of people. He really didn’t want to live but there was something in his head that made him wanted to stay alive and show people he might not be physically strong but he is mentally strong.  
After school Rory was with his friend called Jess they were talking about how she’s getting bullied by the popular girls Jess always tried to help Rory stay alive. She cared about him more than everyone else.
On Saturday Rory was going into town with Leonie they were going to look at clothes and stuff Rory’s phone was on low battery and he received a message from Jess saying “hey=(“ Rory’s phone ran out of battery he was upset what was wrong with Jess. On Wednesday Jess said to Rory she wanted to kill herself Rory thought she was lying and would never do that but he was wrong. Jess couldn’t cope any more she just tied the rope and stood on the chair she rang Rory saying “Hey I can’t cope anymore it’s my time to leave I love you so much but I can’t cope because the bullies and family isn’t helping with my little brother having trouble at school I just can’t live with this anymore I’m so sorry. Please don’t so this you’re not like me you’re a great singer and an amazing author, you going to have an amazing career unlike me mine was going downhill but yours isn’t its going up I tried to help you survive and I hope I succeed but I can’t  keep myself alive anymore. Go and sing your heart out and I love you. See theirs upsides you won’t have to hear me cry anymore so yeah love you.” 
When he got to his gloomy home he put his phone on charge and saw all the messages and voice mail he kept on trying to ring Jess number but it went to voicemail Rory cried and cried the tears were flowing out of his eyes like it was monsoon season in India. He was still trying to get in his mind his best friend has just died he was so upset he decided to go to the special place where he felt safe with Jess and now he had to feel safe on his own there. It was a place where Jess and Rory had most of their fun. It was quite here most of the time and he would go and listen to music in the nicest place possible. 
Rory went to Jess’s family’s house and saw there was two notes one for Rory and one for Jess’s family. Rory hated what he saw and stressed and a couple weeks later he went to the funeral.
Jess’s body funeral has started Rory managed to stay strong until the coffin started to disappear to the gloomy hole in the ground where you can faintly see the coffin. Friends and family through flowers down to the coffin Rory through some pictures of them both together down there and he started to cry. A small tear dripped slowly down Rory’s face and fell on top of the pictures that were on top off the brown coffin. Everyone said there goodbye’s and Eliot Jess’s little brother saw Rory was crying and hugged him and Eliot started to cry as he realised his big sister is gone and he will never see her again.
 
 Chapter 7 “Unknown Brother?”
There was a knock the large door Rory’s mum answered the door there was a 16 year old boy standing there with two bags. Rory’s mum shouted “oh my god you came back!” the teenager replied “yeah I heard I have another brother.” Rory’s mum answered “Yeah he’s called Rory and why did you runaway?” The teen replied “bullies”.
The teenager was Rory’s older brother he was called Robert he went through what Rory was currently go through so he would always be there for him. He ran away from the town for 3 years because of him getting bullied and it was because he liked to shows and stuff like that and people got jealous of him because he was an amazing dancer. He got bullied so much he didn’t want to stay in that town anymore. He had to get away from the people he hated. He wouldn’t cry at school because he was strong enough to hold it in unless he was on his own and then he would burst into tears. 
Robert got introduced to Rory as they didn’t remember each other Robert walked in and sat down on the flower patterned sofa and he said “ Hey, you probably don’t remember me but I’m your big brother and my name is Robert and I love singing, dancing and acting and ill promise I’ll always be here for you.” Rory replied “Why did you leave me and the family Lauren didn’t tell me about you why? Did you tell her not to tell me?” Robert replied “I didn’t want anyone to be scared I didn’t want anyone to be upset do you understand now? And now tell me about you” Rory replied “Well I’m Rory and I’m 12 and I love to sing, dance and act too and I’m auditioning for the school musical too.” 
The next day Robert was enrolled to West Lake Secondary School and was in year 12. Robert and Lauren walked with Rory to school and Rory met his friends and his girlfriend Ashleigh. Rory went to Matthew as he called Rory and he explained “Trevor knows your brother” Rory got worried. Trevor approached the slightly worried Rory and asked “do you know Robert?” Rory replied “yeah he’s my brother” Trevor replied “wow he’s the complete opposite of you he actually smiles and he’s cool unlike you” Matthew shouted “Don’t do this” at Trevor Rory said “no its fine I wanna hear what he wants to say to me.” Trevor replied “ok You have no life he has an amazing one because he has friends and you don’t and he is not depressing.” Trevor pushed Rory against the wall and grabbed him by the throat and whispered into Rory’s ear “you tell Robert I’ll kill you” Robert saw what was happening and ran over and pushed Trevor off Rory and asked Rory and asked what was happening and Rory explained what happened. Robert was upset and had flashbacks of what happened to him when he was younger and the reason he ran away and he got told that Rory ran away but not for long. Robert didn’t want it to happen Rory as he wanted to him to have a successful lie unlike he did at school but he had the main part or would be the choreographer  in the school musicals so there was good points. He was a great choreographer, the best in the town by far. He choreographed in the main theatre in the town and he had loads of successful shows and was mentioned in the newspapers quite a lot. At the auditions for this year’s show “Bully” and Rory auditioned for the main boy character called Jake and Robert auditioned for a dancer. Rory got Jake and instead of a dancer Mrs Potterson the drama teacher asked him to be the choreographer and he was so happy because he loved to make his own dances and he got wanted because he was a dancer in the show to. So Rory and Robert were happy on the way home and excited and Robert was so proud of Rory. They were after school auditions so when they got home Rory ran and told Lauren and his mum and Robert did the same they were so proud of each other. Robert and Rory hugged each other as they were so happy.
